HEADWORD: Undecolic
<hw>Un`de*col"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Undec</ets>ylenic + propi<ets>olic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid,
<chform>C11H18O2</chform>, of the propiolic acid series, obtained
indirectly from undecylenic acid as a white crystalline
substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

